### RemoveDeadStores() {#a626ef0e5d64536a6464fdd4525755eb8}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool StackSlotColoring::RemoveDeadStores (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; MBB)</>}>
RemoveDeadStores - Scan through a basic block and look for loads followed by stores.

If they&#39;re both using the same stack slot, then the store is definitely dead. This could obviously be much more aggressive (consider pairs with instructions between them), but such extensions might have a considerable compile time impact.
